"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-paris-olympics-broadcasters-diverge-on-ai-approach\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Jul 26, 2024; Paris, FRANCE;  General view from inside the Trocadero during the Opening Ceremony for the Paris 2024 Olympic Summer Games along the Seine River.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.177629365541754e-18, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.33779134071626e-24, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rob Schumacher-USA TODAY Sports  REUTERS  Published\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 02:16 AM  Updated\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 02:16 AM  The Paris Olympics will be a showcase of generative AI for American viewers but European audiences will not see a similar approach, a contrast that reflects how global media companies are deliberating over the use of the technology.\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 559, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.581840982166474e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998934758552773, \"rank\": 0.00010650250687789292, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Comcast's NBCUniversal is diving into AI for its U.S. broadcast of the Games, including re-creating the voice of a legendary sportscaster, while Warner Bros.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 741, \"end\": 748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"score\": 0.999999999350166, \"rank\": 6.49909832265217e-10, \"text\": \"Comcast\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\"}, {\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.581840982166474e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\", \"score\": 0.9882547556748427, \"rank\": 0.011870258960734108, \"text\": \"Warner\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery's sports division in Europe said the tech is still too nascent for roles such as sports commentating.\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 1010, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Warner Bros.\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\", \"score\": 0.9882547556748427, \"rank\": 0.011870258960734108, \"text\": \"Warner\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery, which will stream the Games on its Max and discovery+ streaming platforms across Europe, received demos from tech companies to translate speech into other languages but the demos have lacked the emotion that comes with heart-racing sports moments, said Scott Young, senior vice president at Warner Bros.\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1071, \"end\": 1074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Fleischer\", \"score\": 0.6039792007227721, \"rank\": 0.6556797466568374, \"text\": \"Max\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Fleischer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Fleischer\"}, {\"begin\": 1289, \"end\": 1300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Young_(writer)\", \"score\": 0.5590726502055368, \"rank\": 0.6710239651415058, \"text\": \"Scott Young\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Young_(writer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Young_(writer)\"}, {\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\", \"score\": 0.9882547556748427, \"rank\": 0.011870258960734108, \"text\": \"Warner\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WarnerMedia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery Sports Europe.\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In every part of their (demos), it feels like yes, you have translated the words correctly, but you have not translated or narrated the feeling,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, when Italian sprinter Marcell Jacobs stunned the world by winning gold in the men's 100 metres in Tokyo, Italian commentators screamed their reactions, showing the genuine moment of \\\"experts sitting side-by-side, really living out that story,\\\" Young said.\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1542, \"end\": 1549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9947029307004431, \"rank\": 0.005051252048213331, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1559, \"end\": 1573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marcell Jacobs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\"}, {\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999995008549101, \"rank\": 4.988739214328246e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1642, \"end\": 1649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9947029307004431, \"rank\": 0.005051252048213331, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is very hard to automatically generate that.\\\"\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, U.S. audiences will experience AI when they watch the Games on NBC or streaming service Peacock due to a new partnership between NBCUniversal, Google and Team USA.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1886, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.581840982166474e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1918, \"end\": 1921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9853350054109682, \"rank\": 0.008846133100836281, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1984, \"end\": 1996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999991030085242, \"rank\": 8.966725637775966e-07, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 1998, \"end\": 2004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999998957418993, \"rank\": 1.0425450259596335e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 2009, \"end\": 2017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9993714275337204, \"rank\": 0.0005516517071178403, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AI-enhanced Google Map images of the Olympic venues will help viewers get a feel of Paris and NBC's hosts will demonstrate how Google AI search can answer questions about the competitions.\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2032, \"end\": 2038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999998957418993, \"rank\": 1.0425450259596335e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 2104, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999636202, \"rank\": 3.6568452289098475e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9853350054109682, \"rank\": 0.008846133100836281, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2147, \"end\": 2156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_AI\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_AI\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_AI\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBCUniversal will also use generative AI to create personalised daily briefings of the Olympic events, which will be narrated by an AI re-creation of sports commentator Al Michaels' voice.\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2210, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999991030085242, \"rank\": 8.966725637775966e-07, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 2248, \"end\": 2250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.581840982166474e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2342, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.581840982166474e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2379, \"end\": 2390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.808770060420956e-36, \"text\": \"Al Michaels\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost seven million different variations of the daily recaps could be created over the course of the Paris Olympics, NBCUniversal said.\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999991030085242, \"rank\": 8.966725637775966e-07, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The media company has the largest Olympics broadcast rights deal in the world and paid $7.65 billion to air the Games through 2032.\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Broadcasting Services, which produces neutral coverage that can be used by media companies around the world, is also embracing AI to assist with quickly cutting vast amounts of footage into brief highlights, but previously told Reuters it remained wary of the risks of deepfakes and \\\"tampering with reality.\\\"\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2675, \"end\": 2704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympic Broadcasting Services\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\"}, {\"begin\": 2810, \"end\": 2812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.581840982166474e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2911, \"end\": 2918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999998294697, \"rank\": 1.7063747887413386e-10, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given how quickly AI capabilities are advancing, it may not be long until European sports fans see more of the technology.\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3115, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are probably just one Summer Games away from where the real impact will be for us,\\\" Young said.\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The next Summer Games are the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics.\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Olympics  Los Angeles  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3275, \"end\": 3282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3294, \"end\": 3305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999422471, \"rank\": 5.0503033922166104e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3456, \"entities\": []}]}"